main event: Unidentified flying objects were observed by military personnel and civilians in the Cheyenne, Wyoming area over a period of several days.
interesting points: One object was observed to increase in size and brightness as it moved eastward.
Some objects were observed to have a dull red light that flashed on and off.
Observers used binoculars, theodolites, and other equipment to track and observe the objects.
The objects were sometimes mistaken for known celestial objects like Jupiter.
The weather conditions during the sightings were generally clear with occasional clouds.
sighted object: various unidentified flying objects, including glowing orbs, white lights, and objects the size of weather balloons
witnesses: military personnel, civilians, and a U.S. Geological and Geodetic Survey party
photographs: yes, the report includes 4 photographs showing the locations and directions of the sightings
